@startuml C4_Concern_Security
!include https://raw.githubusercontent.com/plantuml-stdlib/C4-PlantUML/master/C4_Component.puml

title YAWL Cross-Cutting Concern - Security & Compliance

Boundary(authentication, "Authentication") {
    Component(oauth, "OAuth 2.0", "Protocol", "Token-based auth")
    Component(mfa, "MFA (TOTP/SMS)", "2FA", "Additional factor")
    Component(session_mgmt, "SessionManagement", "Lifecycle", "Token lifecycle")
}

Boundary(authorization, "Authorization") {
    Component(rbac, "RBAC", "Access", "Role-based")
    Component(abac, "ABAC", "Access", "Attribute-based")
    Component(permission_cache, "PermissionCache", "Performance", "Cached decisions")
}

Boundary(encryption, "Encryption") {
    Component(tls, "TLS 1.3", "Transport", "In-flight encryption")
    Component(aes_256, "AES-256-GCM", "Symmetric", "At-rest encryption")
    Component(rsa_4096, "RSA-4096", "Asymmetric", "Key exchange")
}

Boundary(audit_trail, "Audit & Compliance") {
    Component(immutable_log, "ImmutableLog", "Append-only", "Audit trail")
    Component(compliance_checker, "ComplianceChecker", "Scan", "Policy violations")
    Component(soc_report, "SOC2Reporter", "Report", "SOX 404 compliance")
}

Boundary(secrets_mgmt, "Secrets Management") {
    Component(vault, "VaultIntegration", "Storage", "HashiCorp Vault")
    Component(rotation, "SecretRotation", "Lifecycle", "Auto-rotation")
}

oauth --> mfa: Requires
mfa --> session_mgmt: Manages tokens
session_mgmt --> permission_cache: Checks permissions
rbac --> permission_cache: Evaluates
tls --> encryption: Secures
aes_256 --> vault: Keys from
vault --> rotation: Rotates
immutable_log --> compliance_checker: Scans
compliance_checker --> soc_report: Reports

Note as N1
Security Strategy:

Authentication:
- OAuth 2.0 (standard)
- MFA (TOTP or SMS)
- Session timeout: 1 hour
- Token refresh: 7 days

Authorization:
- RBAC (role-based)
- ABAC (attribute-based, granular)
- Permission caching (5 min TTL)
- Least privilege principle

Encryption:
- TLS 1.3 (in-flight)
- AES-256-GCM (at-rest)
- RSA-4096 (key exchange)
- Certificates from CA

Compliance:
- Immutable audit log (append-only)
- SOX 404 compliance (audit trail)
- GDPR data deletion
- Data classification

Secrets:
- Vault integration
- Auto-rotation (90 days)
- Least privilege access
- Audit logging

Threat Model:
- External: DDoS, brute force, injection
- Internal: privilege escalation, data leaks
- Supply chain: dependency vulnerabilities

Security Testing:
- OWASP Top 10 checks
- Penetration testing (quarterly)
- Dependency scanning (continuous)
- Code review (all PRs)
End note

SHOW_LEGEND()
@enduml
